We need to “extract” the overall sales revenue from the transactions. In our example the main business revenue (“net sales”) is normally the sum of the “after_tax_amount” on all sale‐type transactions. (Other items – deposits, purchases, expenses, etc.– do not count toward the “main business revenue” item.) 

Step‐by‐step, we first go through the table and select every row whose type is “Sale” (ignoring transfer, purchase, expense, etc.) and then sum up the “after_tax_amount” field. (For each sale row the “after_tax_amount” is considered the net revenue from that sale.)

Below are the 17 sale transactions and their “after_tax_amount” amounts:

1. Sale20240103001: 1,341,384.21 
2. Sale20240106004: 1,121,627.04 
3. Sale20240107006: 2,074,189.57 
4. Sale20240110009: 1,011,216.26 
5. Sale20240113011: 2,087,850.23 
6. Sale20240117016:   684,182.05

8. Sale20240119019: 1,964,987.11 
9. Sale20240120020:   685,633.55 
10. Sale20240121022: 2,062,392.24 
11. Sale20240124024: 1,382,680.65 
12. Sale20240127028: 1,315,450.08 
13. Sale20240128030: 2,087,085.30

17. Sale20240204039: 1,360,371.39 

Now we sum them up step‐by‐step:

• After row 1 + row 2: 1,341,384.21 + 1,121,627.04 = 2,463,011.25  
• + row 3: 2,463,011.25 + 2,074,189.57 = 4,537,200.82  
• + row 4: 4,537,200.82 + 1,011,216.26 = 5,548,417.08  
• + row 5: 5,548,417.08 + 2,087,850.23 = 7,636,267.31  
• + row 6: 7,636,267.31 +   684,182.05 = 8,320,449.36  
• + row 7: 8,320,449.36 + 1,050,729.15 = 9,371,178.51  
• + row 8: 9,371,178.51 + 1,964,987.11 = 11,336,165.62  
• + row 9: 11,336,165.62 +   685,633.55 = 12,021,799.17  
• + row 10: 12,021,799.17 + 2,062,392.24 = 14,084,191.41  
• + row 11: 14,084,191.41 + 1,382,680.65 = 15,466,872.06  
• + row 12: 15,466,872.06 + 1,315,450.08 = 16,782,322.14  
• + row 13: 16,782,322.14 + 2,087,085.30 = 18,869,407.44  
• + row 14: 18,869,407.44 + 1,996,342.46 = 20,865,749.90  
• + row 15: 20,865,749.90 + 2,014,126.21 = 22,879,876.11  
• + row 16: 22,879,876.11 + 1,876,172.14 = 24,756,048.25  
• + row 17: 24,756,048.25 + 1,360,371.39 = 26,116,419.64  

Thus the sum of “after_tax_amount” for all sale transactions is 26,116,419.64.

That total is taken as the “Main Business Revenue” (i.e. the income from core operations).
